          "common"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 13
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> the donjon's porter (F8) — an <strong>ash giant</strong> kept servile by constant charms in life, hauling sacrifices down and bodies back up, until Prelate Aruth sacrificed <em>him</em> as part of his own mummy-rising rite. The curse stood the remains back up as a juju zombie that shambled to its old post and has waited five centuries for orders that will never come. <strong>Once he starts bellowing in a fight, @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.prelateAruth0001]{Prelate Aruth} (F10, next door) comes to investigate.</strong> Pursues throughout the donjon but never exits it.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
